Text.Value: Hatched, mostly. Only one remains unbroken, watched over by Varsh Ko'kuu, caretaker of our young.
Step carefully while here. Our hatchery is protected by lethal safeguards. I do not wish to pick your remains from them.
Traps are not built to be avoided. Varsh Ko'kuu designed every one himself, elegantly crafting this room to protect our young.
Amusing.
Kin.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nods at the player in greeting

Text.Value: Watch your feet. Our hatchery does not treat strangers kindly.
I'd like to speak to the caretaker.
You could point out the traps? I'd definitely avoid them then.
Varsh Ko'kuu designed this hatchery to be the perfect birthing place for our warriors: impenetrable to our enemies.
You may speak to him if you wish, but do not approach the egg. Lest you fall foul of me.
Why is the water that colour?
Leave.
You may speak to the Varsh if you wish, but stay away from the egg. There will be no second warning.
Don't worry, I'm leaving.
You linger still?

EditorData.NodeContext: Could throw in a derisive snort or grunt at the end. You don't think much of this decision.

Text.Value: Step carefully, kin. Our hatchery is protected by lethal safeguards - I would hate to see you fall foul of them.
The hatchery is a dangerous place to linger, kin.
Follow the rocks through the acid, but do not approach the egg.
So how can I avoid these traps?
Istik are permitted to view the birthing pools now? These are strange times.
Hatchery? Where are all the eggs?
And do not approach the egg! That would be a transgression too far.
I thought a hatchery would have more eggs?
Most are hatched. Only one remains, monitored by Varsh Ko'kuu, the caretaker of our young.
Water? Our young are not born to water - it is a burning acid.
You will find Varsh Ko'kuu watching over his clutch of one.

Synopsis: A male gith guard, watching over the hatchery where gith eggs are hatched. He's a caustic personality, ready to kill anyone who touches the lone egg in the hatchery.
